---
import SectionLabel from "../../elements/SectionLabel.astro";
import Heading from "../../elements/Heading.astro";
import BodyText from "../../elements/BodyText.astro";
import CTAButton from "../../elements/CTAButton.astro";
---

<section
  class="bg-rh-warm-light dark:bg-rh-warm-dark py-32 md:py-48 px-6 md:px-10"
  id="deliverables-section"
>
  <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-[1400px]">
    <!-- Terminal Header -->
    <div class="deliverables-reveal mb-10">
      <SectionLabel text="> SYS.DELIVERABLES // PLAIN_LANGUAGE" />
    </div>

    <!-- Headline -->
    <Heading class="deliverables-reveal mb-16 max-w-4xl">
      What you <span class="text-rh-ember">get.</span>
    </Heading>

    <!-- Deliverable blocks -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl space-y-20 mb-16">
      <!-- 01 — DIAGNOSE -->
      <div class="deliverables-card">
        <span
          class="block font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-rh-ember mb-4"
          >01 // DIAGNOSE</span
        >
        <h3
          class="font-heading font-black uppercase italic text-2xl md:text-3xl text-rh-ink dark:text-rh-chalk leading-tight mb-6"
        >
          The Human Architecture Review
        </h3>
        <BodyText class="mb-6">
          We map your organization's human architecture across three layers —
          signal, connection, and operating model — and show you exactly where
          it's failing and what it's costing you.
        </BodyText>
        <BodyText class="mb-6">
          This isn't a survey or a workshop. It's a systems-level diagnostic
          built on 25 years of engineering infrastructure and 15 years of
          studying how humans actually connect at scale.
        </BodyText>
        <BodyText>
          You walk away with a complete architectural blueprint: what's broken,
          what to fix first, and what the ROI looks like when you do.
        </BodyText>
      </div>

      <!-- 02 — DESIGN -->
      <div class="deliverables-card">
        <span
          class="block font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-rh-ember mb-4"
          >02 // DESIGN</span
        >
        <h3
          class="font-heading font-black uppercase italic text-2xl md:text-3xl text-rh-ink dark:text-rh-chalk leading-tight mb-6"
        >
          Your Architecture, Built
        </h3>
        <BodyText class="mb-8">
          Based on the blueprint, we design and build the specific human systems
          your organization is missing.
        </BodyText>

        <!-- Signal -->
        <div
          class="border-l-2 border-rh-ember/30 pl-6 md:pl-8 mb-6"
        >
          <p
            class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-rh-ember/60 mb-3"
          >
            SIGNAL
          </p>
          <p
            class="text-base md:text-lg text-rh-ink/70 dark:text-rh-chalk/70 leading-relaxed"
          >
            If the right people can't find you — we build your signal
            architecture: the alignment between your mission, your message, and
            the people who need to hear it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Connection -->
        <div
          class="border-l-2 border-rh-ember/30 pl-6 md:pl-8 mb-6"
        >
          <p
            class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-rh-ember/60 mb-3"
          >
            CONNECTION
          </p>
          <p
            class="text-base md:text-lg text-rh-ink/70 dark:text-rh-chalk/70 leading-relaxed"
          >
            If people arrive but don't stay — we design your connection
            infrastructure: the environments, rituals, and peer-to-peer systems
            that create belonging that sustains itself.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Operating Model -->
        <div
          class="border-l-2 border-rh-ember/30 pl-6 md:pl-8 mb-8"
        >
          <p
            class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-rh-ember/60 mb-3"
          >
            OPERATING MODEL
          </p>
          <p
            class="text-base md:text-lg text-rh-ink/70 dark:text-rh-chalk/70 leading-relaxed"
          >
            If your culture breaks at scale — we redesign your operating model:
            how your people coordinate, trust, and build together in a way that
            compounds instead of fracturing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <BodyText>
          Every organization's architecture is different. We don't sell
          templates. We design systems.
        </BodyText>
      </div>

      <!-- 03 — TRANSFER -->
      <div class="deliverables-card">
        <span
          class="block font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-rh-ember mb-4"
          >03 // TRANSFER</span
        >
        <h3
          class="font-heading font-black uppercase italic text-2xl md:text-3xl text-rh-ink dark:text-rh-chalk leading-tight mb-6"
        >
          You Own It. It Compounds.
        </h3>
        <BodyText class="mb-6">
          We train your team to operate the architecture independently. Then we
          step back.
        </BodyText>
        <BodyText class="mb-6">
          The systems we design are built to be self-reinforcing — peer-driven,
          community-sustained, getting stronger with every cycle. This isn't a
          retainer you pay forever. It's infrastructure that compounds in value
          after we leave.
        </BodyText>
        <BodyText>
          No agency dependency. No consultant lock-in. Architecture you own.
        </BodyText>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="deliverables-reveal">
      <CTAButton href="/how-we-work" variant="contrast">
        See How Engagements Work →
      </CTAButton>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  import { gsap } from "gsap";
  import { ScrollTrigger } from "gsap/ScrollTrigger";
  gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);

  gsap.fromTo(
    ".deliverables-reveal",
    { opacity: 0, y: 50 },
    {
      opacity: 1,
      y: 0,
      duration: 1,
      stagger: 0.3,
      ease: "power3.out",
      scrollTrigger: {
        trigger: "#deliverables-section",
        start: "top 70%",
      },
    },
  );

  gsap.fromTo(
    ".deliverables-card",
    { opacity: 0, y: 40 },
    {
      opacity: 1,
      y: 0,
      duration: 0.8,
      stagger: 0.2,
      ease: "power3.out",
      scrollTrigger: {
        trigger: "#deliverables-section",
        start: "top 55%",
      },
    },
  );
</script>
